  "text": "Data from Brazilian Southeastern Bight (BSB) were collected during four acoustic cruises for biomass assessment (ECOSAR project; summers of 2008 and 2010; springs of 2008 and [CITATION_1] ) of the R/V Atlântico Sul on the shelf area between São Tomé Cape (21ºS) and Santa Marta Cape (28ºS). Those cruises surveyed the area for Sardinella brasiliensis and other small pelagic species such as the argentine anchovy. Data from southern Brazil were collected under the Anchoita project during the spring of 2010. In all cruises, ecointegration surveys were carried out with an EK-500 scientific echo sounder. A mid-water trawl was used to identify and assess fish species composition detected by the echo sounder.",
